\f0\fs28 \cf2 for f to be continuous, we fix both epsilon positive and 
\f1\b \cf2 a 
\f2\b0 \cf2 in S before obtaining the value of r. So the choice of r might depend on 
\f1\b \cf2 a 
\f2\b0 \cf2 as well as on epsilon. Uniform continuity means that for each epsilon positive, the value r positive that we obtain can be chosen independently of the point 
\f1\b \cf2 a
\f2\b0 \cf2 . This is a subtle difference.}

