\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 orthogonal
\f1\b0 \cf2  ( two vectors x and y such that <x,y> = 0), 
\f0\b \cf2 orthonormal
\f1\b0 \cf2  (a collection of vectors \{e_n: n in S\} in V is called orthonormal if ||e_n|| = 1 for all n in S and <e_n, e_m> = 0 for any different n and m in S.)}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue-Bold;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red6\green53\blue51;}
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 lemma:
\f1\b0 \cf2  \{e_n\} an orthonormal set, alpha_n are real coefficients, if w = sum alpha_n times e_n, then for each j, <w, e_j> = alpha_j. for any vector v, v-sum(<v, e_i>e_i is orthogonal to each e_j, where i is from 1 to n.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue-Bold;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red6\green53\blue51;}
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 corollary:
\f1\b0 \cf2  \{e_n\} is a finite orthonormal set, x is in span\{e_1,\'85e_n\} then x can be written uniquely as sum(<x, e_i>e_i) where i is from 1 to n. further, all orthonormal sets are linearly independent.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue-Bold;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red6\green53\blue51;}
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 corollary: 
\f1\b0 \cf2 in a finite-dimensional vector space, an orthonormal set is a basis if and only if it is maximal with respect to being an orthonormal set.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue-Bold;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red6\green53\blue51;}
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 The Gram-Schmidt Process}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red6\green53\blue51;}
