\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 proposition: 
\f1\b0 \cf2 the functions \{1, square root 2 *cosnx, square root 2 *sinnx; n>=1\} form an orthonormal set in PC[-pi, pi] with this inner product.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue-Light;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red6\green53\blue51;\red7\green53\blue52;}
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural

\f0\fs28 \cf2 f ~ A_0 + sum(A_n*cosnx + B_n*sinnx\cf3 ), where A_0 = 1/2pi * integral (from -pi to pi) f(t)dt, and for n >= 1, A_n = 1/pi * integral(from -pi to pi) f(t)cosntdt, B_n = 1/pi * integral(from -pi to pi) f(t)sinntdt.\cf2  }

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue-Light;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 HelveticaNeue-Bold;}
