\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Parseval\'92s Theorem: 
\f1\b0 \cf2 let S be a subset of N and E = \{e_n : n in S\} be an orthonormal set in a Hilbert space H. Then the subspace M = spanE^bar consists of all vectors x = sigma(alpha_n * e_n) where the coefficient sequence (alpha_n) belongs to l^2. Further, for x in H, then x in M iff the Bessel\'92s inequality is hold.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
