\f0\fs28 \cf2 a family of functions F mapping a set S belongs to R^n into R^m is 
\f1\b \cf2 equicontinuous at a point 
\f2\b0 \cf2 a in S if for every epsilon > 0, there is an r > 0 such that ||f(x) - f(a)|| < epsilon whenever ||x - a|| < r and f is in F.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
