\f0\fs28 \cf2 def: 
\f1\b \cf2 compact 
\f2\b0 \cf2 (a metric space X is compact if every open cover of X has a finite subcover), 
\f1\b \cf2 sequentially compact 
\f2\b0 \cf2 (a metric space X is sequentially compact if every sequence of points in X has a convergent subsequence), 
\f1\b \cf2 totally bounded 
\f2\b0 \cf2 (a metric space X is totally bounded if for every epsilon > 0, there are finitely many points x_1, \'85, x_k in X such that the ball centred at those points is an open cover.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1265\cocoasubrtf190
